still fighting full-time with a very serious plumbing issue on the shed, after two pipes deciding to blow up together, unable to repair your-usual-disaster previous installation i had no choice but rebuild the entire water distribution system from zero, good news is we expect to have water running at home this night, which is a welcome change since all our basic watering needs for the last two weeks were satisfied with old reliable' buckets

in the meantime, i managed to write some tests to print strings using the rom subroutine with the rst 010h call, i think my prefered way to write numbers is with this format since it's flexible enough to specify all bases in the same way, also able to store code in custom-defined memory sections with multiple orgs, and organizing code splitting from the start in multiple files with imports, one of the hardest 'tech debts' of the zxelda C version, so far so good, i've been copying lots of practices from other homebrews as learning material, next stop is learn how to pass parameters, since for two different strings now i have two entire separated calls that are the same except loading the string pointer in the first line
